flowRoot.flowPara: Our project website and documentation can be found at www.openstreetmap.org. Signing up is quick, easy, and of course, free of charge. We also have a wiki with a wealth of project information, topic- and country-specific mailing lists, and a Q&A help system if you get stuck.

OpenStreetMap's servers are run by a not-for-profit organisation in England called the OpenStreetMap Foundation, and there are many national organisations like OpenStreetMap UK CIC, OpenStreetMap US, or FOSSGIS e.V. in Germany. Our data is published under the "Open Database License 1.0" (ODbL). Anyone can share, adapt, and create works from our data freely, provided that they give attribution to "OpenStreet-Map contributors", and share any adapted databases under the same license.

The map above shows an OpenStreetMap rendering of London. Just like the map on the other side and the globe on the front page, it was created with Open Source software. Many Open Source software projects have been created specially for OpenStreetMap.
This flyer is based on work by Andy Allan,
and was updated and printed by FOSSGIS e.V.
